[SN]TITLE[SN]
Wales to return to Portugal training camp before Serbia match in June

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Wales will return to the Vale do Lobo resort in Portugal for a training camp before their 2018 World Cup qualifier against Serbia on 11 June.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Chris Coleman's squad used the complex on the Algarve last May as part of their preparations for Euro 2016.
Wales are third in their qualifying group after four consecutive draws, four points behind leaders Serbia with five games remaining.
Gareth Bale and Neil Taylor are suspended for the game in Belgrade.
